  "prompt": "What is the primary disadvantage of using timestamps?",
  "response": "The primary disadvantage of using timestamps is the potential for clock synchronization issues. In distributed systems, different machines may have clocks that are not perfectly synchronized, leading to problems such as incorrect ordering of events, inconsistency in data, and difficulty in debugging and tracing operations across the system. Additionally, relying solely on timestamps can also result in vulnerabilities to clock drift or malicious manipulation of time settings.",
